<h2 id="who-its-for">👤 Who Each Platform Is For</h2>

<strong>Choose Buildium if:</strong>
- You manage under 500 residential units
- Your portfolio is single-family, multifamily, or HOA-focused
- You need to onboard staff quickly without extensive training
- Budget efficiency matters more than advanced features
- You don't manage commercial properties
- Your ownership structures are straightforward

<strong>Choose AppFolio if:</strong>
- You manage 500+ units or plan to scale aggressively
- You have mixed residential and commercial portfolios
- High inquiry volume makes AI leasing valuable
- You need sophisticated accounting (CAM, accruals, complex entities)
- Your team is tech-savvy and can absorb a learning curve
- You want best-in-class mobile capabilities for field staff

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Scaling Consideration:</strong> We've seen operators start on Buildium, hit 400-500 units, and migrate to AppFolio. The migration is painful—budget 4-6 weeks and significant staff time. If you're confident about growth past 500 units within 2-3 years, starting on AppFolio may save you a migration headache later.
</div>

<h2 id="integration-ecosystem">🔌 Integration Ecosystem</h2>

Both platforms connect with common industry tools, but depth varies.

Buildium integrates with Happy Inspector for inspections, Nelco for checks and forms, and various ILS sites for listings. The integration library is smaller, and some connections require Zapier workarounds. Check our [property management integrations guide](/articles/property-management-software-integrations) for compatibility details.

AppFolio offers more native integrations: Zillow Rental Manager, HappyCo, PayNearMe for cash payments, and deeper accounting software connections. The open API is more robust, making custom integrations feasible for operators with technical resources.

<h2 id="final-verdict">🏆 Final Verdict: Buildium vs AppFolio 2026</h2>

After years of supporting operators on both platforms, our recommendation is clear:

<strong>For portfolios under 500 units with straightforward residential properties, Buildium delivers the best value.</strong> You'll spend less, train faster, and have everything you need for core property management. The premium you'd pay for AppFolio won't generate proportional returns at this scale.

<strong>For portfolios approaching or exceeding 500 units—especially with commercial properties or complex ownership—AppFolio justifies its premium.</strong> The accounting depth, AI automation, and reporting capabilities create operational efficiencies that compound as you scale.

The decision isn't about which platform